definitions.definition: A deciduous tree , Carya illinoinensis , of the central and southern United States , having deeply furrowed bark , pinnately compound leaves , and edible nuts .
A smooth , thin - shelled , edible oval nut of this tree.
A half of the edible portion of the inside of this nut.
